03:04.688 --> 03:08.390
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

03:15.966 --> 03:19.968
Sorry about breakfast, baby.
Lena was up all night.

03:20.003 --> 03:22.370
Yeah, I-I heard.

03:24.441 --> 03:27.642
So, Craig tells me you're
bangin' your teacher.

03:27.678 --> 03:29.344
Is that true?

03:35.752 --> 03:37.652
You know, I am not interested

03:37.688 --> 03:39.788
in every detail of your sex life,

03:39.823 --> 03:42.957
but this is one you
definitely should've told me.

03:44.061 --> 03:47.495
The last thing we need is
some bullshit at your school.

03:47.531 --> 03:51.599
No, she, um... She
wouldn't say anything.

03:51.635 --> 03:53.334
Or she'd lose her job.

03:53.370 --> 03:55.770
You're gonna have to break it off.

03:55.806 --> 03:59.808
Okay, baby? And I'm not asking.

04:04.848 --> 04:06.648
BAZ: Because you're her best friend,

04:06.683 --> 04:09.284
and she hasn't been back
in three days, that's why.

04:09.319 --> 04:10.885
No. No.

04:10.921 --> 04:14.756
No, no one saw anything. I told you.

04:14.791 --> 04:16.558
(LAUGHS)

04:16.593 --> 04:19.094
What the hell is that supposed to mean?

04:19.129 --> 04:20.261
Ah.

04:20.297 --> 04:22.664
We did not get in a fight, Krystal!

04:22.699 --> 04:23.998
Well, did Cath say we did?

04:24.034 --> 04:26.067
'Cause I'm telling you, I swear to God,

04:26.103 --> 04:27.769
if there's something
you're not telling me...

04:27.804 --> 04:30.805
No, please, don't hang up.
Hey, Krystal, do...

04:30.841 --> 04:33.575
(LAWN MOWER RUNNING IN DISTANCE)

04:37.714 --> 04:40.849
She still hasn't picked up
her paycheck at the bar.

04:40.884 --> 04:41.950
(GRUNTS)

04:41.985 --> 04:43.451
Did you try calling her again?

04:43.487 --> 04:46.121
No, her voicemail's full.

04:46.156 --> 04:47.355
I don't get it.

04:47.390 --> 04:49.591
No credit card hits, not even for gas.

04:49.626 --> 04:51.526
Well, if she took Smurf's
money like she...

04:51.561 --> 04:54.129
Smurf's full of shit, okay?

04:54.164 --> 04:55.530
Yeah.

04:58.335 --> 05:00.301
Just say it.

05:00.337 --> 05:03.238
This is somehow my fault, isn't it?

05:03.273 --> 05:05.273
I know that's what you're thinking.

05:05.308 --> 05:07.342
That's not what I'm thinking.

05:10.347 --> 05:13.581
♪

05:14.351 --> 05:15.583
(BUZZER)

05:15.619 --> 05:17.986
(GARAGE DOOR OPENER WHIRRING)

05:28.231 --> 05:30.632
(BRAKE SQUEALING)

05:34.237 --> 05:36.571
(TIRES SCREECH)

05:45.248 --> 05:47.615
(SIRENS CHIRPS)

05:55.058 --> 05:57.692
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

05:59.863 --> 06:01.229
Where you going?

06:01.264 --> 06:02.897
I'm going to school.

06:02.933 --> 06:05.233
Get your ass back in that house

06:05.268 --> 06:06.534
in case the money shows up.

06:06.570 --> 06:08.036
Look, if I stay in the house all day,

06:08.071 --> 06:10.538
someone's gonna get suspicious.

06:10.574 --> 06:13.374
I said I'd text you
when something happens,

06:13.410 --> 06:14.676
and I will.

06:14.711 --> 06:17.645
Yeah. That was three days ago.

06:17.681 --> 06:19.848
Well, I don't know what the holdup is.

06:19.883 --> 06:21.649
We've been very understanding.

06:21.685 --> 06:23.818
When you begged us not to wear the wire,

06:23.854 --> 06:25.720
'cause she's walking in
on you all the time,

06:25.755 --> 06:27.322
all that hanging out by the pool.

06:27.357 --> 06:29.424
- Did we force you?
- No.

06:29.459 --> 06:31.726
We're trying to keep you safe.

06:32.963 --> 06:34.963
But if you're lying to us,

06:34.998 --> 06:36.931
trying to figure a way out
of doing the right thing,

06:36.967 --> 06:39.500
you will regret it for
the rest of your life.

06:39.536 --> 06:42.537
I'll text you.

06:45.075 --> 06:46.674
Okay.

06:51.781 --> 06:53.748
- Any?
- No.

06:53.783 --> 06:55.850
What about Craig and Deran?

06:55.886 --> 06:57.085
(LAUGHS)

06:57.120 --> 07:00.088
That's it, huh? Straight to business?

07:00.123 --> 07:01.256
Cath goes AWOL.

07:01.291 --> 07:03.691
Are we supposed to
forget about our money?

07:03.727 --> 07:06.027
- It'll move.
- So you said.

07:06.062 --> 07:06.961
Two days ago.

07:06.997 --> 07:08.830
It's a normal delay. It'll move.

07:08.865 --> 07:11.566
And what if it doesn't move?

07:11.601 --> 07:14.435
Do you have a Plan B?

07:14.471 --> 07:16.838
I'm gonna talk to Lena again.

07:16.873 --> 07:19.540
What? No, you are not!

07:21.478 --> 07:23.511
(SIGHS)

07:27.050 --> 07:30.351
Okay, you took a bath.
Then Mommy did book time.

07:30.387 --> 07:33.154
But after she left the room,
are you sure no one came over?

07:33.189 --> 07:35.056
Maybe... Maybe you heard
Mommy on the phone?

07:35.091 --> 07:35.990
I fell asleep.

07:36.026 --> 07:37.492
Nothing woke you up? Think hard.

07:37.527 --> 07:38.726
Did it feel like a dream?

07:38.762 --> 07:40.495
What did you dream?

07:40.530 --> 07:41.829
I was in Mommy's car.

07:41.865 --> 07:43.331
- Car. Good.
- Okay, okay, okay.

07:43.366 --> 07:44.366
Where were you going?

07:44.367 --> 07:45.767
A man was driving.

07:46.903 --> 07:49.470
Who? Do you remember who?

07:49.506 --> 07:51.139
No? What about his voice?

07:51.174 --> 07:52.874
Can you hear his voice?

07:52.909 --> 07:55.610
Lena, where were you going?
Mommy wasn't there.

07:55.645 --> 07:57.445
What do you mean she wasn't there?!

07:57.480 --> 07:58.713
Come on, Lena, think!

07:58.748 --> 08:01.249
- Baz. That's enough.
- (SIGHS)

08:02.218 --> 08:04.686
Come here, sweetie. Come here.

08:04.721 --> 08:06.187
You know what I have?

08:06.222 --> 08:08.690
I have a secret hiding
place for cookies.

08:08.725 --> 08:10.091
And if you can find it,

08:10.126 --> 08:13.161
I'll let you have as
many as you want, okay?

08:15.098 --> 08:16.397
(URINATING)

08:16.433 --> 08:18.733
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

08:25.442 --> 08:27.375
(SIGHS)

08:27.410 --> 08:30.645
(ELECTRONIC GUNFIRE)

08:30.680 --> 08:32.813
You gonna break the screen. Please stop.

08:32.849 --> 08:34.881
I'm trying to get warm.

08:34.918 --> 08:38.052
I caught a chill sleeping in
this shit-box last night.

08:39.556 --> 08:40.855
(SIGHS)

08:40.890 --> 08:42.690
Well, maybe Baz is wrong about all this,

08:42.726 --> 08:44.525
and the money never moves.

08:44.561 --> 08:46.060
I mean, what if the military just...

08:46.096 --> 08:47.929
You know, what if they don't
recycle the fry grease?

08:47.964 --> 08:50.732
Maybe they just dump it in
the ocean or something.

08:50.767 --> 08:54.369
You hear about them paying
like 400 bucks for a hammer?

08:54.404 --> 08:56.270
God damn it!

08:56.306 --> 09:00.141
Maybe you and me could run for Congress,

09:00.176 --> 09:01.209
clean it all up.

09:01.244 --> 09:04.712
Bet Smurf would help us buy some votes.

09:06.216 --> 09:07.081
Or not.

09:07.117 --> 09:09.717
Jesus, what are you doing?

09:09.753 --> 09:12.020
Well, I can't just sit here.

09:13.123 --> 09:15.823
Don't you think it's a
bad idea to get amped?

09:15.859 --> 09:18.126
You know, while we're just sitting here?

09:21.798 --> 09:24.665
(SNORTS)

09:25.969 --> 09:30.671
How dare you inflict your
bullshit on that child.

09:31.608 --> 09:33.808
Where is she?

09:33.843 --> 09:36.644
She's outside coloring.

09:36.679 --> 09:39.614
Maybe when you get your
head out of your ass,

09:39.649 --> 09:42.683
you could join her, act like a dad.

09:43.920 --> 09:46.654
Thanks for the parenting advice, Smurf.

09:46.689 --> 09:49.857
Cath packed a bag,

09:49.893 --> 09:51.993
and she took her passport.

09:52.028 --> 09:54.362
Now, what is it you're not seeing?

09:54.397 --> 09:56.964
Could you do me a favor and
just stay out of this, please?

09:57.000 --> 09:58.733
Maybe she found out about Lucy.

09:58.768 --> 10:00.601
Maybe she always knew

10:00.637 --> 10:03.271
and finally she just said, "Screw it.

10:03.306 --> 10:05.873
I'll give him a taste
of his own medicine."

10:05.909 --> 10:07.141
If Cath was stepping out of me,

10:07.177 --> 10:08.910
she wouldn't leave Lena
alone in the house.

10:08.945 --> 10:10.878
She wouldn't do it, not ever!

10:10.914 --> 10:15.550
Okay, baby. She's not
stepping out on you.

10:15.585 --> 10:18.486
She's gone for good.

10:18.521 --> 10:20.955
She wanted a new life.

10:20.990 --> 10:24.725
She took 10K from behind the dryer.

10:24.761 --> 10:26.427
Did you see her take the money?

10:26.463 --> 10:28.429
Jesus, baby. Give me a break.

10:28.465 --> 10:30.098
I'll give you a break. What
about Deran and Craig?

10:30.133 --> 10:32.500
No, they could never take it.
They wouldn't do that.

10:32.535 --> 10:33.768
Or maybe you took it, Smurf.

10:33.803 --> 10:35.770
Watch it, Barry.

10:35.805 --> 10:38.372
You know, you can drop the bullshit.

10:38.408 --> 10:39.740
You hate Cath.

10:39.776 --> 10:41.776
You've been trying to get
rid of her for years.

10:41.811 --> 10:43.778
And I don't give a shit what you think.

10:43.813 --> 10:45.313
I know something happened.

10:45.348 --> 10:48.216
She wouldn't leave. Not without Lena.

10:59.162 --> 11:00.461
Uh!

11:00.497 --> 11:03.798
I thought Craig was the one
known for drinking before noon.

11:03.833 --> 11:06.200
(WATER RUNNING)

11:11.274 --> 11:12.673
She all right?

11:12.709 --> 11:13.774
No.

11:13.810 --> 11:16.611
(WATER SHUTS OFF)

11:16.646 --> 11:19.447
Doesn't help her father's an asshole.

11:21.484 --> 11:23.417
I'm out of moves here, man.

11:23.453 --> 11:27.421
I mean, I don't know what to do.
What am I supposed to do?

11:27.457 --> 11:29.190
I don't know.

11:43.072 --> 11:45.973
That's the money we gave Vin.
How do you have that?

11:46.009 --> 11:47.375
The job was going down.

11:47.410 --> 11:49.644
I couldn't let you lose your focus.

11:49.679 --> 11:50.878
How'd you get it, Smurf?

11:50.914 --> 11:52.380
He jumped the gate. He was drunk,

11:52.415 --> 11:56.050
saying that he didn't want to
be paid off like some whore.

11:56.085 --> 11:57.285
And you didn't tell us?

11:57.320 --> 11:59.120
Obviously, I thought I handled it.

11:59.155 --> 12:00.721
Well, what did he say?

12:00.757 --> 12:02.223
He didn't say anything,

12:02.258 --> 12:04.725
just a river of shit out of his mouth.

12:04.761 --> 12:05.927
Did he threaten Cath?

12:05.962 --> 12:08.262
He threatened all of us.

12:08.298 --> 12:10.431
What did he say about Cath?!

12:10.466 --> 12:13.000
He said you thought he'd
bend over like a whore?

12:13.036 --> 12:14.602
Wait till you see what
he does to your wife.

12:14.637 --> 12:16.871
Jesus Christ.

12:32.219 --> 12:34.519
I'm scared, Alexa.

12:35.422 --> 12:37.021
You know, I...

12:37.086 --> 12:40.187
I think their plan's still on
track, but I can't be sure.

12:46.662 --> 12:51.098
Yates told you to have
sex with me, didn't she?

12:51.133 --> 12:53.600
So you'd get me to talk.

12:56.005 --> 12:57.337
And if you did,

12:57.373 --> 13:00.173
you'd walk away from
your drug charge, right?

13:01.744 --> 13:04.144
Don't lie to me.

13:07.216 --> 13:09.549
Yes.

13:09.585 --> 13:12.019
I'm sorry.

13:12.054 --> 13:14.521
But now that you don't...

13:16.058 --> 13:19.026
Is this real?

13:19.061 --> 13:22.663
You know, it feels real.
I might just be crazy.

13:22.698 --> 13:24.318
No. No.

13:24.358 --> 13:26.625
No, you're not crazy.

13:26.660 --> 13:28.994
You're not.

13:35.503 --> 13:38.370
(INTERCOM RINGS)

13:41.075 --> 13:43.142
(BEEPS)

13:49.556 --> 13:51.523
What are you doing here?

13:51.548 --> 13:52.728
I need to talk to Baz.

13:52.753 --> 13:54.119
Baz isn't here.

13:54.650 --> 13:56.350
Yeah, well, he's ignoring my calls.

13:56.386 --> 13:57.852
Because he's not a moron.

13:57.887 --> 14:00.821
Now, if you're here to tell me
why our money hasn't moved,

14:00.857 --> 14:02.289
let's have it.

14:02.325 --> 14:04.058
Well, the pickup was
scheduled a couple days ago,

14:04.093 --> 14:05.760
but there's been a little delay.

14:05.795 --> 14:07.228
How long?

14:07.263 --> 14:11.732
That depends. I'm the
one that delayed it.

14:11.768 --> 14:15.569
Now, look. I've got a lot at stake here.

14:15.605 --> 14:18.205
I'm not saying you don't, Janine,

14:18.241 --> 14:19.907
but, I mean, honestly,

14:19.942 --> 14:22.309
could you have done this without me?

14:22.345 --> 14:24.278
I don't think so.

14:24.313 --> 14:26.881
So I want a bigger cut.

14:26.916 --> 14:29.483
I want $150,000, not $100,000.

14:29.519 --> 14:32.353
And I'm not trying to gouge you.

14:32.388 --> 14:34.922
Really, I mean, I just want to be fair.

14:34.957 --> 14:36.590
I want to feel respected.

14:36.626 --> 14:39.293
So 150K.

14:39.328 --> 14:42.797
And that pickup happens ASAP.

14:44.834 --> 14:47.301
(HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING)

14:56.078 --> 14:57.311
Stop.

14:57.346 --> 14:59.146
Can't, bro, best part coming up.

14:59.182 --> 15:01.148
Stop! Please, stop!

15:01.184 --> 15:02.750
- (MUSIC SHUTS OFF)
- Asshole!

15:02.785 --> 15:04.418
Yo, turn it back on, or you're
going out the windshield!

15:04.454 --> 15:06.520
- (MUSIC RESUMES)
- No! Are you kidding me?!

15:06.556 --> 15:08.022
I'm not kidding you now, man!

15:08.057 --> 15:09.190
You're acting like a child.

15:09.225 --> 15:10.825
You're literally acting like a child.

15:10.860 --> 15:12.326
Oh, God!

15:12.361 --> 15:14.228
(MUSIC SHUTS OFF)

15:14.263 --> 15:17.164
(AIRPLANE PASSING OVERHEAD)

15:17.200 --> 15:19.700
My God.

15:19.735 --> 15:21.302
- You hear that?
- (EXHALES SHARPLY)

15:21.337 --> 15:23.337
You hear it? Come on. You hear it?

15:23.372 --> 15:24.638
Huh?

15:24.674 --> 15:26.607
No. Exactly.

15:26.642 --> 15:28.509
When was the last time we were on a job

15:28.544 --> 15:30.377
and Baz didn't call to give us shit?

15:30.413 --> 15:32.980
Hmm? Never.

15:33.015 --> 15:36.016
You know, maybe Cath taking
off has its benefits.

15:36.052 --> 15:37.585
Yeah, what's up with that?

15:37.620 --> 15:40.187
And Cath knew about Lucy and Baz.

15:40.223 --> 15:41.255
Can't be that.

15:41.290 --> 15:43.924
Maybe her kid is his.

15:43.960 --> 15:45.259
Shit, you think?

15:45.294 --> 15:46.527
(GPS BEEPING)

15:46.562 --> 15:48.662
- What is that? Hey.
- Huh?

15:48.698 --> 15:49.864
That's the GPS.

15:49.899 --> 15:51.432
It's the GPS. Where is it?

15:51.467 --> 15:52.833
It was on the dash.

15:52.869 --> 15:54.235
What, did you snort it up your nose?
Come on.

15:54.270 --> 15:55.503
- Oh, here it is.
- Give me it, give me it.

15:55.538 --> 15:56.904
Oh, shit. There's coke on it.

15:56.939 --> 15:59.673
Okay, give me it.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.342
Yes. Yes. We're a go.

16:01.377 --> 16:03.277
It's heading out the gate
at Vandegrift. Come on.

16:03.312 --> 16:04.712
Let's do this.

16:04.747 --> 16:06.680
- (ENGINE STARTS)
- Come on, man, let's go, man.

16:06.716 --> 16:09.483
♪

16:13.256 --> 16:15.589
(TIRES SCREECH)

16:17.994 --> 16:20.628
♪

16:43.419 --> 16:45.753
What do you want?

16:45.788 --> 16:47.788
Is this your job now?

16:47.823 --> 16:50.124
Yeah.

16:50.159 --> 16:52.126
Yeah, you happy for me?

16:52.161 --> 16:53.427
Smurf said you came to the house,

16:53.462 --> 16:54.995
threw the money we gave you at her.

16:55.031 --> 16:59.767
Should've done a lot worse
with her shotgun in my face.

17:05.207 --> 17:07.407
What?

17:07.443 --> 17:10.144
You impressed her.

17:10.179 --> 17:12.746
I told her what you did for me inside,

17:12.781 --> 17:15.115
and she agreed to cut you in.

17:15.151 --> 17:17.217
One job.

17:17.252 --> 17:19.286
One job.

17:19.321 --> 17:21.555
See how it goes.

17:21.590 --> 17:24.290
So clean up if you want.
I'll meet you out back.

17:24.327 --> 17:26.727
It's going down now.

17:30.066 --> 17:33.233
♪

17:33.269 --> 17:35.402
Look, look. There's that... See?

17:35.438 --> 17:37.538
- Nice.
