24:14.619 --> 24:17.020
Hmm? Did you kill her?

24:17.055 --> 24:19.989
At least be man enough to
tell me where the body is.

24:21.293 --> 24:24.160
(GRUNTING)

24:25.697 --> 24:30.333
(EXHALING SHARPLY)

24:33.038 --> 24:37.640
I killed two men in my life... Two.

24:37.676 --> 24:42.345
One in Bakersfield. He
broke into my trailer.

24:42.380 --> 24:45.949
One in Joshua Tree. He came
after me with a knife.

24:45.984 --> 24:51.054
That's the one I did time for.

24:55.427 --> 24:58.261
I never touched your wife.

24:58.296 --> 25:03.833
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

25:03.868 --> 25:07.236
You're going to tell me
what you did with her.

25:07.272 --> 25:08.972
- (SPITS)
- Or you're going to die here.

25:09.007 --> 25:10.573
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

25:10.608 --> 25:12.809
Then get it over with, punk.

25:15.280 --> 25:17.714
(BOTH GRUNTING)

25:25.590 --> 25:27.824
(GULPING)

25:45.577 --> 25:47.010
He's still breathing.

25:47.045 --> 25:50.613
Well, we can't let him live.

25:50.648 --> 25:52.415
You go home. I'll take care of it.

25:59.758 --> 26:01.958
DERAN: Did you talk to Baz and Pope yet?

26:01.993 --> 26:03.593
SMURF: They'll be back soon.

26:03.628 --> 26:05.628
CRAIG: Well, they'll be stoked.

26:05.663 --> 26:07.897
Okay, something fancy.

26:07.932 --> 26:09.999
Tequila with ice.

26:10.035 --> 26:12.168
You're light 12 grand.

26:12.203 --> 26:13.669
Guess we missed a few packs.

26:13.705 --> 26:16.172
Didn't you double-check
inside the drums?

26:16.207 --> 26:17.240
Oh, our bad.

26:17.275 --> 26:18.775
I guess when we were sliding around like

26:18.810 --> 26:20.476
human hockey pucks in
toxic food waste...

26:20.512 --> 26:23.679
What do you think would
happen if they found it?

26:23.715 --> 26:26.382
Coded Federal Reserve cash.

26:26.418 --> 26:29.185
That will lead them to Building 15,

26:29.220 --> 26:33.056
then to Admiral Paul, and then to us.

26:33.091 --> 26:37.060
I want you two to go back and
find where that oil is recycled.

26:37.095 --> 26:38.795
All right, Smurf, stop!

26:38.830 --> 26:41.030
Who the hell do you think
you're talking to?!

26:41.066 --> 26:42.365
We took it. It's in my room.

26:42.400 --> 26:43.499
What are you doing, man?

26:43.535 --> 26:45.234
I felt like we deserved a little bonus.

26:45.270 --> 26:47.070
Oh, really, now?

26:47.105 --> 26:49.272
Way to have some balls, bro.

26:49.307 --> 26:52.475
Go get it. Now!

26:56.681 --> 26:58.347
- I'm the one that folds?
- Oh, yeah, like you weren't gonna?

26:58.383 --> 27:01.184
Couple of idiots, still
think that they could...

27:04.722 --> 27:06.422
J?

27:06.458 --> 27:09.992
Is there somewhere you can hide this?

27:12.931 --> 27:14.931
There are two cops waiting
for me to text them

27:14.966 --> 27:16.232
when I think it's the
right time for them

27:16.267 --> 27:18.768
to come in and raid the house.

27:44.481 --> 27:46.548
Hey, my Lena-roo.

27:46.583 --> 27:51.353
Come on. Lie down next to me.

27:51.388 --> 27:55.724
♪ The day is my enemy ♪

27:55.759 --> 28:00.629
♪ The night, my friend ♪

28:02.833 --> 28:05.400
We're not gonna listen to any noise.

28:09.606 --> 28:10.639
Police! Let me see your hands!

28:10.674 --> 28:11.873
Don't move!

28:11.909 --> 28:12.774
- Let me see your hands!
- Hands up!

28:12.810 --> 28:16.311
Get on your feet! Now!

28:16.346 --> 28:18.747
Lay down on your stomach!

28:18.782 --> 28:20.882
All right, face down! Face down!

28:20.918 --> 28:22.150
Do what he says!

28:22.186 --> 28:22.984
You heard him!

28:23.020 --> 28:27.422
Look left. Don't move!

28:27.458 --> 28:31.259
Ma'am, on your feet. Now.

28:31.295 --> 28:33.628
Put your hands behind your head.

28:33.664 --> 28:35.464
Davis, grab the kid.

28:35.499 --> 28:37.365
Don't move, ma'am.

28:37.401 --> 28:38.467
I'm right here, Lena.

28:38.502 --> 28:40.502
Grandma Smurf?

28:40.537 --> 28:42.838
Yeah, baby. Right here.

28:42.873 --> 28:45.907
♪ The day is my enemy ♪

28:45.943 --> 28:51.813
♪ The night my friend ♪

29:23.680 --> 29:25.914
(SIGHS)

29:53.577 --> 29:56.812
♪

30:20.904 --> 30:24.372
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

30:24.408 --> 30:26.708
J said the cash would be in the kitchen.

30:26.743 --> 30:28.777
It should be right here.

30:28.812 --> 30:30.979
So should he.

30:31.014 --> 30:33.014
The little girl's here.

30:33.050 --> 30:37.152
And Cath used to bitch about
leaving her with Smurf.

30:37.187 --> 30:38.887
What if they're on to us, Sandra? Huh?

30:38.922 --> 30:41.823
What if... what if they
took care of both of them?

30:41.859 --> 30:44.292
We got nothing. No cash, no kid.

30:44.328 --> 30:45.827
Just tear up the walls if you have to.

30:45.863 --> 30:47.729
Hey. No. No, stop. Don't. Don't.

30:47.764 --> 30:49.497
That is beyond the
scope of this warrant.

30:49.533 --> 30:52.000
This thing already stinks.
Let's not make it any worse.

30:52.035 --> 30:55.303
Where's the money? Where is it?

30:55.339 --> 30:57.339
I don't know what you're talking about.

30:57.374 --> 30:59.007
But if you'd like a ham sandwich,

30:59.042 --> 31:00.775
the fixings are in the fridge.

31:00.811 --> 31:03.511
Where's J? Your grandson?

31:03.547 --> 31:05.347
Where's he?

31:05.382 --> 31:07.449
Have Baz and Pope got him?

31:07.484 --> 31:11.286
They lay a hand on that
kid, so help me God...

31:11.321 --> 31:15.323
I think I'd like to call my lawyer.

31:36.747 --> 31:38.313
You little shit.

31:38.348 --> 31:42.550
You chose the wrong side, asshole.

31:42.586 --> 31:43.385
Right pocket.

31:43.420 --> 31:44.252
Shut up!

31:44.288 --> 31:48.123
Right pocket of my hoodie.

31:48.158 --> 31:51.960
Yeah, I recorded that on
my iPhone earlier today.

31:51.995 --> 31:56.531
Right after Alexa raped me.

31:56.566 --> 32:00.368
See, I'm only 17. My mom just died.

32:00.404 --> 32:03.038
Alexa was my teacher. I
thought I could trust her.

32:03.073 --> 32:04.572
I didn't think she'd be preying on me

32:04.608 --> 32:07.242
just so you'd let her walk
away from a drug charge,

32:07.277 --> 32:09.411
just to get dirt on my family.

32:09.446 --> 32:12.113
Make me tell lies about them.

32:13.283 --> 32:16.184
That's not the only copy.

32:16.219 --> 32:21.656
I want you to stay away from
me, stay away from my family,

32:21.692 --> 32:24.059
or I'll send that to your
boss in the D.A.'s office.

32:24.094 --> 32:29.097
Excuse me?

32:29.132 --> 32:31.099
Are you going to charge my grandson?

32:31.134 --> 32:35.470
'Cause it's almost dinnertime.

32:35.505 --> 32:37.872
I won't forget this.

32:37.908 --> 32:41.910
Yeah, I won't forget about it, either.

32:41.945 --> 32:45.780
I remember you.

32:45.816 --> 32:50.518
Me sitting in the corner playing
with some shitty little toy,

32:50.554 --> 32:53.955
watching you come over to work my mom.

32:53.991 --> 32:56.157
She'd beg you to leave.

32:56.193 --> 32:59.160
She cried and, oh, man,
you'd just do anything,

32:59.196 --> 33:00.462
even offer to score for her,

33:00.497 --> 33:03.365
just so you could get what you wanted.

33:03.400 --> 33:06.468
But you never got it, did you?

33:06.503 --> 33:10.038
See, my mom,

33:10.073 --> 33:13.641
she hated them.

33:13.677 --> 33:16.044
But she hated you more.

33:18.782 --> 33:23.985
In the end, she's a Cody.

33:24.021 --> 33:26.421
And I'm a Cody, too.

34:01.736 --> 34:03.669
That's all of it.

34:03.705 --> 34:07.206
You sure? You didn't hide
anything down your pants?

34:08.909 --> 34:10.751
Been kind of a day, huh?

34:10.775 --> 34:11.775
Yeah.

34:12.213 --> 34:14.647
You all right?

34:15.485 --> 34:18.487
Yeah, I'm okay.

34:23.024 --> 34:24.790
Any trouble getting rid of...?

34:24.826 --> 34:26.859
No, I took care of it.

34:30.565 --> 34:34.500
That one was unexpected...
J and the cops.

34:34.534 --> 34:35.634
Was it?

34:35.670 --> 34:37.203
Hey, thanks for helping out, bud.

34:37.237 --> 34:39.672
Really appreciate it.

34:39.706 --> 34:45.706
Uh, we... we got a visitor
and I'm kind of indisposed.

34:45.813 --> 34:47.213
It's Paul.

34:47.248 --> 34:50.216
(CLEARS THROAT)

34:52.853 --> 34:54.219
Let him in.

34:54.255 --> 34:56.621
- I'll be right there.
- Okay.

35:14.242 --> 35:16.008
You shouldn't be here.

35:16.043 --> 35:18.611
Well, it's come to my attention
that somebody hijacked

35:18.646 --> 35:20.713
one of my recycling trucks.

35:20.748 --> 35:22.448
And I thought that was kind of weird,

35:22.483 --> 35:24.617
because who the hell does that, right?

35:24.652 --> 35:26.919
(LAUGHS)

35:30.024 --> 35:33.659
$150,000, like we agreed.

35:33.694 --> 35:37.630
(SCOFFS) You can't really
be that dumb, can you?

35:37.665 --> 35:39.732
Do you think I would let
you walk out of here

35:39.767 --> 35:41.066
with that much cash?

35:41.102 --> 35:43.469
What if the police stop you?

35:46.174 --> 35:47.773
I just want my money.

35:47.809 --> 35:49.008
And you'll get it...

35:49.043 --> 35:52.545
In three weeks in a locker
in the bus station.

35:52.580 --> 35:55.614
You better not be trying to screw me.

35:55.650 --> 35:59.919
Or what?

35:59.954 --> 36:02.655
What are you going to do?

36:06.360 --> 36:09.028
Why don't you get the
hell out of my house?

36:09.063 --> 36:10.529
Take the back door.

36:10.565 --> 36:12.331
And if the cops stop you,

36:12.366 --> 36:14.867
you tell them you were
looking for your daughter.

36:14.902 --> 36:19.305
That you had a big fight
over birth control.

36:19.340 --> 36:21.674
You're a piece of work, you know that?

36:26.280 --> 36:28.514
I said the back door.

36:40.194 --> 36:41.660
(GIRL LAUGHING)

36:41.696 --> 36:43.362
(MUFFLED RAP MUSIC PLAYS)

36:43.397 --> 36:45.965
♪ To all the punks in their
panties, the real live is here ♪

36:46.000 --> 36:49.001
♪ It's the fella ya hear,
and I'm smelling ya fear ♪

36:49.036 --> 36:51.470
♪ One thing that I know ♪

36:51.506 --> 36:53.806
♪ That I control our flow, so let's go ♪

36:53.841 --> 36:56.542
♪ And it's something you can't hide ♪

36:56.577 --> 36:58.611
♪ The adrenaline burns inside ♪

36:58.646 --> 37:01.280
♪ Yo, it's the rush ♪

37:16.163 --> 37:18.998
You should've told me right away.

37:20.701 --> 37:23.669
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry.

37:23.704 --> 37:25.771
Why were you sure I wouldn't
have one of the boys

37:25.806 --> 37:30.342
put a bullet in your head and
dump your body in the ocean?

37:30.378 --> 37:33.012
I wasn't.

37:33.047 --> 37:34.947
You know,

37:34.982 --> 37:36.982
even with all the shit that
my mom put you through,

37:37.018 --> 37:39.485
you... you still paid
our rent, you know?

37:39.520 --> 37:43.756
She sure as hell wasn't doing it, so...

37:43.791 --> 37:47.026
I figured you'd give me a chance.

37:52.967 --> 37:54.733
You lied.

37:54.769 --> 37:58.571
And you were an idiot,
even after I warned you.

37:58.606 --> 38:00.005
This shit stops now

38:00.041 --> 38:03.475
or you can pack your little
kit bag and hit the road.

38:08.716 --> 38:11.984
You got some brass balls, kid.

38:16.624 --> 38:19.158
You play your cards right,

38:19.193 --> 38:22.928
you can do well with us.

38:24.131 --> 38:27.366
I have something for you.

38:38.012 --> 38:41.046
A man should have a gun.

38:44.051 --> 38:45.084
Uh...

38:45.119 --> 38:48.454
Try "Thank you."

38:48.489 --> 38:49.688
Thank you.

38:50.825 --> 38:53.292
Now go get rid of that
pea shooter you have

38:53.327 --> 38:56.662
hidden up in your bedroom vent, okay?

38:56.697 --> 38:59.031
Pope used to hide shit
up there all the time

38:59.066 --> 39:00.265
when he was your age.

39:00.301 --> 39:03.469
He still thinks I don't know.

39:03.504 --> 39:08.641
Just keep it away from Lena.

39:37.071 --> 39:40.639
Did you see Lena? Bet she
sleeps till morning.

39:40.675 --> 39:46.178
If J was talking to the
cops, maybe Cath wasn't.

39:51.185 --> 39:53.052
Lena sat in the cop car

39:53.087 --> 39:58.657
while her mother met her friend.

39:58.693 --> 40:01.460
And then Cath stole $10,000 from us,

40:01.495 --> 40:05.664
packed a suitcase to leave the country.

40:05.700 --> 40:09.268
Andrew, the cops were
working both of them.

40:09.303 --> 40:13.272
Cath caved, J didn't.

40:13.307 --> 40:16.108
I want my share of the job.

40:20.581 --> 40:24.416
(STERNLY) I want my share of the job.

40:24.452 --> 40:26.518
Absolutely. Once a month like always.

40:26.554 --> 40:29.188
No!

40:29.223 --> 40:31.056
I want all of it.

40:31.092 --> 40:33.692
I'm getting my own place.

40:33.728 --> 40:34.993
That's not going to happen.

40:35.029 --> 40:36.495
I'm not asking. I did what you wanted.

40:36.530 --> 40:38.831
You're giving me that money.

40:52.346 --> 40:56.582
Okay.

40:56.617 --> 40:58.717
Just don't tell any of your brothers...

40:58.753 --> 41:01.620
seem like a real asshole.

41:05.760 --> 41:09.328
SMURF: Oh, go ahead. Take
it out on me, right?

41:09.363 --> 41:10.829
I'm your mother.

41:10.865 --> 41:16.201
I can handle it. That's my job.

41:16.237 --> 41:20.873
But really, Andrew, you hate yourself.

41:20.908 --> 41:22.708
You hate yourself because of the way

41:22.743 --> 41:26.245
you let her play you
for years and years.

41:26.280 --> 41:28.080
Oh, shut up. Shut up.

41:28.115 --> 41:31.517
And yes, I set up your Folsom buddy Vin

41:31.552 --> 41:34.286
to get us out of this jam.

41:34.321 --> 41:38.423
But you can't blame me for
running your mouth in prison.

41:38.459 --> 41:43.195
You shut up!

41:43.230 --> 41:47.232
God, you are so twisted and
such a goddamn coward.

41:47.268 --> 41:50.836
If you had any balls at all, you
would've told Baz the truth,

41:50.871 --> 41:53.038
but, no, you just told me.

41:53.073 --> 41:56.175
Do you know why?

41:56.210 --> 42:00.445
Because you were worried
he'd choose her.

42:00.481 --> 42:02.614
And that's your biggest fear.

42:02.650 --> 42:05.083
That Baz would leave you... Baz.

42:08.889 --> 42:11.824
But what about me?

42:11.859 --> 42:14.793
What about me, your real son?

42:17.431 --> 42:19.631
You use me...

42:19.667 --> 42:21.967
to do the dirty work like you always do.

42:22.002 --> 42:24.736
Yes, all the dark and terrible shit

42:24.772 --> 42:26.772
that you're too afraid to do yourself.

42:26.807 --> 42:29.208
And you call that being a mother?

42:33.113 --> 42:36.348
You're sicker than I'll ever be.

43:14.622 --> 43:18.123
(GARAGE DOOR OPENS)

43:18.826 --> 43:21.126
(ENGINE STARTS)

43:36.610 --> 43:39.878
♪

44:52.386 --> 44:55.053
Rachel?

45:21.148 --> 45:24.082
People call me "Smurf" now.

45:27.755 --> 45:30.288
(GASPING)

45:30.324 --> 45:32.357
(GUNSHOT)

45:51.378 --> 45:54.413
♪

46:17.004 --> 46:19.037
DERAN: Smurf's still sleeping in?

46:19.073 --> 46:21.106
She could've left us a
note or something, Jesus.

46:21.141 --> 46:26.011
Probably wrecked dealing with Lena.

46:26.046 --> 46:27.646
Oh. Uh, sorry, you can go.

46:27.681 --> 46:30.082
- (CLEARS THROAT)
